    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix XML output formatting in QualityOfService dump function\n\n### Summary\nThe dump_quality_of_service_xml() function was producing malformed XML output due to element names containing spaces. This caused issues when trying to parse the debug output with standard XML parsers.\n\nThe function has been updated to use proper camelCase element names without spaces, making the XML well-formed and compatible with standard parsers.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/IES/QualityOfService.c`: Updated XML element names in dump_quality_of_service_xml() to use camelCase instead of spaces\n- Root element changed from `<Quality Of Service>` to `<QualityOfService>`\n- All field elements updated from `<Field name>` format to `<FieldName>` format\n- Maintained all existing functionality while fixing XML formatting\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen calling dump_quality_of_service_xml() during NAS debugging, the XML output contained element names with spaces which caused parsing errors in XML processing tools. The malformed XML would fail validation against standard XML parsers.\n\nAfter this fix, the XML output can be properly parsed by standard XML tools and validators.\n"
}